The '''2007<U+2013>08 Notre Dame Fighting Irish men's basketball team''' represent the [[University of Notre Dame]] in the [[college basketball]] [[2007-08 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|season of 2007-08]], competing in the [[Big East Conference]]. The team is led by eighth-year [[head coach]], [[Mike Brey]], and play their home games in the [[Edmund P. Joyce Center]] in [[Notre Dame, Indiana]].

The previous year's team finished with a 24&ndash;8 record and 11&ndash;5 record in Big East games. They competed in the [[2007 Big East Men's Basketball Tournament|2007]] [[Big East Men's Basketball Tournament]] and received an [[at-large bid]] in the [[2007 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament|2007 National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) Division I men's basketball tournament]], where they lost their first game. The team graduated its two top-scorers between the seasons, but returned three [[starting lineup|starters]] and added four [[Recruiting (college athletics)|recruits]] for 2007-08. They were picked to finish ninth in the Big East.

Notre Dame began the season playing an out of conference schedule that included the [[Paradise Jam Tournament]] and reached their conference games with a 10&ndash;2 record. Currently the team is [[2007-08 NCAA Division I men's basketball rankings|ranked]] 14<sup>th</sup> in the [[AP Poll|Associated Press (AP)]] Poll and 15<sup>th</sup> in the [[Coaches Poll]], and has a 24&ndash;7 record overall. The 14&ndash;4 record in conference places the team tied in second in the conference, and is the most conference wins in the history of the school. Dating to 2006, the team won 37&nbsp;consecutive home games, the second longest active winning streak in the nation.

==Preseason==
{{seealso|Rules of basketball|Glossary of basketball terms}}
The 2006-07 Notre Dame team finished their season with a 24&ndash;8 record that included a loss in the first round of the NCAA tournament.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://und.cstv.com/sports/m-baskbl/recaps/031607aaa.html|title=Irish Fall To Eagles In NCAA First Round|date=March 16, 2007|publisher=University of Notre Dame|accessdate=2008-02-24}}</ref> The Irish made the NCAA tournament for the first time since 2003 and the 24&nbsp;wins tied the 1973-74 team for the most ever wins at Notre Dame.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://und.cstv.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/031107aac.html|title=Men's Basketball Returns To The Big Dance, Will Face Winthrop In Spokane|date=March 11, 2007|publisher=University of Notre Dame|accessdate=2008-02-24}}</ref> Because of the team's accomplishments, Mike Brey was named Big East Coach of the Year.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://und.cstv.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/030607aab.html|title=Mike Brey Named BIG EAST Coach Of The Year|date=March 6, 2007|publisher=University of Notre Dame|accessdate=2008-02-24}}</ref>

===Roster changes and recruiting===
Notre Dame lost its two top scorers, [[Russell Carter (basketball)|Russell Carter]] and [[Colin Falls]], to graduation in 2007.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://und.cstv.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/041107aaa.html|title=Carter, Falls Tabbed Co-MVPs At Annual Banquet|publisher=University of Notre Dame|date=April 11, 2007|accessdate=2008-02-24}}</ref> In addition to Carter and Falls, freshman, Joe Harden, who played in only 14&nbsp;games throughout the season, decided to transfer from Notre Dame.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://und.cstv.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/061907aaa.html|title=Joe Harden Leaves Men's Basketball Program|date=June 19, 2007|publisher=University of Notre Dame|accessdate=2008-02-24}}</ref> Kyle McAlarney, a junior, who was suspended for most of the 2006-07 season because of an arrest,<ref>{{cite news|author=Parrish, Gary|url=http://www.sportsline.com/collegebasketball/story/9950117/1|title=Something stinks ... and it isn't coming from McAlarney's car|publisher=CBS Sportsline|date=January 23, 2007|accessdate=2008-02-24}}</ref> was re-instated onto the team.<ref>{{cite news|author=Hine, Chris |url=http://media.www.ndsmcobserver.com/media/storage/paper660/news/2007/11/08/Sports/KMacs.Comeback.The.Black.Jersey-3087371.shtml |title=K-Mac's comeback: The black jersey|work=The Observer|publisher=University of Notre Dame|date=November 8, 2007|accessdate=2008-02-24}}</ref> With McAlarney's return, the team returned four former [[starting lineup|starters]].<ref name="Outlook">{{cite news|url=http://und.cstv.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/110607aac.html|title=Notre Dame Faces St. Edward's Tonight in the Final Exhibition Tuneup|date=November 6, 2007|publisher=University of Notre Dame|accessdate=2008-02-24}}</ref>

In addition to the returning players, the Irish signed four [[Recruiting (college athletics)|recruits]] for their new class. Although the class was not highly ranked, it included two three&ndash;star athletes.

