===Pre-season outlook===
With three former starters that had experience in the NCAA Tournament, the Irish hoped to have another run to the tournament.<ref>{{cite news|author=Khorey, Chris |url=http://media.www.ndsmcobserver.com/media/storage/paper660/news/2007/10/11/Sports/Mens-Basketball.With.KMac.Back.Irish.Set.Sights.On.Return.To.Big.Dance-3026229.shtml |title=Men's Basketball: With K-Mac back, Irish set sights on return to Big Dance|date=October 11, 2007|work=The Observer|publisher=University of Notre Dame|accessdate=2008-02-24}}</ref> However, with only five returning upperclassmen, including only one senior, the Big East's coaches picked the team to finish ninth in the conference.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://und.cstv.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/102407aaa.html|title=Notre Dame Picked To Finish Ninth In The 2007-08 BIG EAST Men's Basketball Season|date=October 24, 2007|publisher=University of Notre Dame|accessdate=2008-02-24}}</ref> Even so, the team entered the season with a 20&nbsp;home game winning streak, dating to the end of the 2005-06 season.<ref name="Outlook" />

==Regular season==
===Roster===
{{seealso|Basketball positions}}
Notre Dame began the season with 12&nbsp;[[athletic scholarship|scholarship]] players and two [[walk-on (sports)|walk-on]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://und.cstv.com/sports/m-baskbl/mtt/nd-m-baskbl-mtt.html|title=2007-08 Roster|publisher=University of Notre Dame|accessdate=2008-02-22}}</ref> Rob Kurz, the only senior on the team, was named [[team captain]] prior to the season.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://und.cstv.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/110207aaa.html|title=Rob Kurz Named Captain For 2007-08 Men's Basketball Season|publisher=University of Notre Dame|date=November 2, 2007|accessdate=2008-02-22}}</ref> In the 2006-07 season, Tory Jackson took over the [[point guard]] position after Kyle McAlarney was suspended. With McAlarney's return, Brey dissolved the position and both are listed as guards.<ref name="KMac">{{cite news|author=Rittenberg, Adam|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/ncb/columns/story?id=3267338|title=McAlarney hopes to atone for one poor choice|publisher=ESPN|date=March 12, 2008|accessdate=2008-03-12}}</ref>

